- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely because the paper focuses on wireless local area network (WLAN) and proposes a technique to combat shadowing.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible because the paper deals with millimeter wave communication, which is often used for high-speed multimedia applications.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible because the paper mentions computation complexity and proposes a suboptimal scheme that may have hardware implementation implications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible because the paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of a wireless communication system.
